  "text": "Verdurmen et al the treatment with 8 out of 10. The observed effects on pain intensity, pain disability, and quality of life can be considered encouraging for the elderly. An explanation for the more limited effect on somatic symptoms might be that our elderly SSD patients suffered from more comorbid medical conditions than their younger counterparts, which can account for a smaller margin of improvement than among the younger SSD patients. A higher somatic comorbidity among elderly SSD patients was also found in other studies. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] However, we did not find that amount of chronic medical conditions influenced treatment outcome.",
